The paper deals with a communication system that involves multiple receivers collecting packets transmitted by a user population, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a novel type of diversity to the conventional Slotted Aloha scheme, which is a system-level enhancement and falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the problem of having receivers forward the full set of collected packets to a final gateway using the minimum possible amount of resources, which is related to Multimedia (cs.MM) and Performance (cs.PF) sub-categories.
